Package: RAMEN
Title: Dynamic Bipartite Additive and Multiplicative Effects Models
Version: 1.1.2
Authors@R: person("Jing", "Luo", email = "luo.1405@osu.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements dynamic additive and multiplicative effects (AME)
    models for bipartite network data using a temporal alternating least
    squares (ALS) algorithm. Supports row, column, and dyadic covariates,
    temporal smoothing of latent factors, and multi-start initialization
    to reduce sensitivity to local optima in the first period.
